column5: Just checking to see if any knows of any boat launchs might be close to opening any where on Simcoe  .
~~~~I'm a looken also, send me a PM, and I'm a thunk I know of one that could be open
Semi solid ice 1 hour ago at tiffin. Still doesn't look good for a while yet.
Back it in at the bridge in Angus.

Thank you Brian , i think am to big to go in there . I find it hard to beleive how fast it happens when it starts , guess it wont be to much longer if we have this weather a bit longer . Thank you too Dave .
If you really need a perch feed,fish the shore line open spots.
Lots of open water down here......boat coming out of winter sleeping next Wed or Thursday........then maybe some CALICO fishing, weather permitting......
CALICO = Crappie. I be all over that.C&R.
whooh, thanks for clarifying. I thought BB was out fishing for cats. Now that's a Redneck!
You guys are looking for an open boat launch, and I was driving on the lake today  Crazy season this has been.  S.
Here kitty kitty kitty.....

There are a couple of spots in Oro that you could put a small boat in now. Just past the 7th on ice road is one spot and the other would be the 6th line. You would need a 4x4 due to the snow and ice on the road to the water, but the shoreline is pretty much free of ice. I haven't checked the 9th line boat launch so not sure how it is looking.  Rob C
Awsome RC , i'll have to take ride over that way tomorrow .
You failed to mention the windshield tag thats required.

Heyyyy !  ....lol    	If theres no docks at thease spots , not sure cause i've never used them before , my boat might be to big to launch at them . If there any thing like the spot at the sixth , i now i can't launch there .
I wonder if Gull Rock Marina would let you launch?Years ago kept a boat there.
I dont mind if i have to wait till the ice gets out of the bay , its those nice sunny days till then that worry me .... lol .
nope. Golden Medonte now. Private.  I think there is more open water now around shanty bay.  lol!  Maybe too early for joking around about that.
This is my first year to have a boat in the spring ,  when dose it start to happen generally at the Tiffen st Launch ?
I would think Ron this year especially,you'll see boats out as soon as it's safe to do so. Ice fishing being short for lakers and whities for most.
